==English==

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# {{slang}} Shortened form of [[difference]]
#:''A peach and an apricot? What's the diff?''
# {{computing}} Any program which compares two files or sets of files an outputs a description of the differences between them.
# {{computing}} The output of a diff program.  A [[diff file]].

===Transitive Verb===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|diff||}}

# {{computing}} To run a diff program.
# {{computing}} To produce a description of changes made to a collection of files.  To produce a [[patch file]].

===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}

# {{computing}} A program, historically part of the [[Unix]] [[operating system]], which compares two files or sets of files an outputs a description of the differences between them.

